Class Discount

java.lang.Object
CSC540.WolfWR.models.DomainObject
CSC540.WolfWR.models.Discount
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
@Entity public class Discount extends DomainObject
Represents a discount applied to a specific Merchandise product. This entity is used to track the discount percentage, the start and end dates for when the discount is applicable, and the associated product.

The Discount entity is mapped to the database with composite primary key consisting of the product ID and the discount start date, which is handled by the Discount.DiscountID class.

The Discount object contains information about the product being discounted, the percentage of discount, and the duration of the discount (start and end dates).
